	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=17167&amp;mid=108517636518882">Who gets this?</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=17167&amp;mid=108517636518882#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Fri, May 21st 5:54 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=324827"><span id=" ">Joesnellenberge</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">24 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.17]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p> Uena Said-<br/><br/>I'm sorry but I have to call BS. I have NEVER heard a truly convincing argument for DKP. The common statement is that it's fairer than rolling, which I accept, but to which I propose this: is it MORE FUN to encourage guildies to hoard points and slowly save up for the better gear (also motivating them to NOT spend points on the mediocre gear - why would they waste money on stuff that's only a minor upgrade when they'll get the uber stuff later?), or would it be more enjoyable to encourage guildies to raid with the thought in their mind that they every so often might get a nice drop? I know what I run in my guild, and though we're not 'uber' as you define it, it certainly works for us.<br/><br/><br/><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;   The reason people do DKP is theres the SELECT group, though of no fault of there own, are greedy.  They only go to the raids where they can roll on something, therefore the GUILD is hurt when they dont go... IF you offer them a reward to go (DKP) then heck You would see your monks killing thunder all the time (Thunder drops no monk lewtz) But heck why would they want to go if they cant roll (remember this is the greedy people!) BUT if they get dkp they can buy BETTER upgrades... DKP doesnt hurt anyone, at least not from my knowledge, I only raided on weekends in a DKP guild for a month, I amassed 25 dkp, enough to buy one VERY nice piece of equipment (this would be about 25dkp in a raiding guild, so if you spend one week, raid with your guild, and are on a DKP system... you get a major upgrade a week! Also, when a guild is on a DKP system, the people are willing to raid with people they dont get along with, raid where they dont want to, and are able to kill mobs that your &quot;average&quot; everyday guild could not (NOW there ARE some exceptions!) But on a whole, I for one will never join a /random guild agian. Its to much for luck, heck you could raid 3 months in a row every night with them and not win... It's not fair.</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Joesnellenberge Phoenix<br/></td></tr>
